### pgAdmin Web Interface Tests
### Test PostgreSQL web-based admin interface

### 1. Main Interface Health Check
GET http://localhost:8082
Content-Type: text/html

### 2. Login Page Check
GET http://localhost:8082/login
Content-Type: text/html

### 3. Browser API (after login - requires session)
# Note: This endpoint requires authentication
# Use browser to login first with admin@admin.com / admin
GET http://localhost:8082/browser/
Content-Type: application/json

### Expected Results:
# 1. Should return pgAdmin web interface HTML
# 2. Should return login form HTML
# 3. Requires browser login session to work

### Note: pgAdmin requires web-based login for most functionality
### These tests verify the service is accessible and the login page loads
### Full testing requires browser interaction at http://localhost:8082

### To test PostgreSQL connection manually:
# 1. Go to http://localhost:8082
# 2. Login with admin@admin.com / admin  
# 3. Add server with:
#    - Name: Local PostgreSQL
#    - Host: postgres (container name) or host.docker.internal
